Proposal finalized: {'Name': 'spectral_precision_routing', 'Title': 'Deterministic Spectral Estimators for Training-Free Precision Routing in Neural Networks', 'Short Hypothesis': 'Deterministic spectral estimators can optimize precision routing in neural networks without requiring training, reducing computational overhead while maintaining performance.', 'Related Work': 'Existing work on precision routing often relies on heuristic methods or training-dependent optimization, which can be computationally expensive and lack theoretical guarantees. Recent advances in spectral analysis and training-free representation geometry provide a foundation for deterministic approaches, but these have not been applied to precision routing. This proposal distinguishes itself by leveraging deterministic spectral estimators for precision routing, offering a mathematically transparent and computationally efficient alternative.', 'Abstract': 'Precision routing in neural networks is crucial for optimizing computational efficiency and performance. However, existing methods often rely on heuristic or training-dependent optimization, which can be computationally expensive and lack theoretical guarantees. This paper proposes a novel approach that leverages deterministic spectral estimators to optimize precision routing without requiring training. By analyzing the curvature and feature entanglement of neural network representations, we develop a training-free routing protocol that reduces computational overhead while maintaining performance. Our experiments demonstrate the effectiveness of this approach on standard benchmarks, showing significant improvements in computational efficiency and robustness. This work bridges the gap between theoretical spectral analysis and practical neural network optimization, offering a mathematically transparent and computationally efficient alternative to existing methods.', 'Experiments': ['Use deterministic spectral estimators to diagnose curvature and feature entanglement in neural network representations.', 'Develop a training-free precision routing protocol based on spectral analysis.', 'Validate the protocol on standard neural network benchmarks (e.g., CIFAR-10, ImageNet).', 'Compare computational efficiency and performance against existing precision routing methods.', 'Evaluate robustness through systematic ablation studies and multi-seed variance quantification.'], 'Risk Factors and Limitations': ['The effectiveness of spectral estimators may vary across different architectures and datasets.', 'The proposed method may introduce additional computational overhead for spectral analysis.', 'The approach may not generalize to highly complex or non-linear neural network architectures.', 'Empirical validation may reveal limitations in the theoretical guarantees of the proposed method.']}
